from numpy import absolute
from numpy import around
In [19]:

In [20]:
cv=RepeatedKFold(n_splits=10,n_repeats=3,random_state=1)  #assigning a cross validation method
In [21]:
scores = cross_val_score(model, x, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=-1)  #executing the crossvalidation machine learning and obtaining the R Squared score
In [22]:
n=len(y)          #obtaining the adjusted R-Squared
p=len(xcolumns)
adj_scores=1-(1-scores)*(n-1)/(n-p-1)
In [23]:
scores_MSE = cross_val_score(model, x, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=-1, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error') #obtaining the mean square error
In [24]:

In [25]:
scores_RMSE= cross_val_score(model, x, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=-1, scoring='neg_root_mean_squared_error') #obtaining the root mean squared error
